newspaper_data.title: Rock City
newspaper_data.entry: On June 8, 1990, the Los Angeles Times wrote about the hard rock fans and musicians on the Strip developing a “distinctive community, complete with its own dialect, attire, attitudes, rock star accessory marts, guitar and drum supermarkets, [and] nightclubs.” Such nightclubs that are frequented are Gazzarri’s at 9039 Sunset Boulevard, the Roxy at 9009 Sunset Boulevard, the Rainbow at 9015 Sunset Boulevard, and Whiskey A Go Go at 8901 Sunset Boulevard.

social_cultural_data.entry: Gazzaris--part of the hair metal scene on Sunset in the 80s
Sites featured in the "Freak Out! Hot Spots" map included in early versions of the 1966 Mothers of Invention/Frank Zappa album "Freak Out!"
